  "prompt": "I'm in love with my FWB, should I stop having sex with him cause every time we have sex I get more attached to him?",
  "response": "It's understandable to develop deeper feelings for someone when you're in a physical relationship, especially if you have a strong emotional connection with your friend with benefits (FWB). If you feel that your feelings are becoming overwhelming or that you want something more serious than what the FWB arrangement offers, it may be worth considering a few options:\n\n1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**: Take some time to think about what you truly want. Are you hoping for a committed relationship, or do you want to maintain the status quo? Understanding your feelings can help inform your next steps.\n\n2. **Communicate**: If you're comfortable, consider talking to him about your feelings. He may feel similarly, or he may not. Open communication can help you both understand where you stand.\n\n3. **Set Boundaries**: If you decide to continue the FWB arrangement but want to manage your feelings, consider setting boundaries regarding emotional intimacy and frequency of physical intimacy.\n\n4. **Take a Break**: If you believe that having sex is making you more attached and you\u2019re unsure about the relationship, taking a break from physical intimacy might help you gain clarity.\n\nUltimately, prioritize your emotional well-being and make the choice that feels right for you.",
